      • queryEventful

        public static void queryEventful(java.lang.String location,
                 int radius,
                 int page,
                 nl.group11.planplan.APIHandler.Callback<java.util.List<nl.group11.planplan.EventfulEvent>> callback,
                 nl.group11.planplan.APIHandler.Callback<org.json.simple.JSONObject> miscCallback)
        Queries Eventful using settings, and providing two Callbacks for this methods to pass back the query results.
        Parameters:
        location - location parameter of the query, in the form of a city name like "Eindhoven" or "New York".
        radius - the radius parameter of the query in kilometers.
        page - the page number parameter of the query. This indicates which page of the total search results will be returned.
        callback - a Callback instance, whose onItem() method will be called with a List of EventfulEvents, representing the resulting events from the query.
        miscCallback - a Callback instance, whose onItem() method will be called when the JSON result from the query comes in. This raw JSON result will be passed to the onItem() call. This feature can be used in places where more information about the query needs to be used, other than the actual events

      • queryGooglePlaces

        public static void queryGooglePlaces(java.lang.String location,
                     int radius,
                     java.lang.String type,
                     nl.group11.planplan.APIHandler.Callback<java.util.List<nl.group11.planplan.GooglePlace>> callback)
        Queries Google Places Web Service API given query parameters
        Parameters:
        location - location parameter used in the query. Needs to be formatted as follows: latitude,longitude
        radius - radius parameter of the query in meters.
        type - the type parameter of the query. This can have any of the values as given at https://developers.google.com/places/supported_types
        callback - Callback instance, whose onItem() method will be called with a List of GooglePlaces, representing the query results, when available.

      • queryGooglePlaces

        public static void queryGooglePlaces(java.lang.String location,
                     int radius,
                     java.lang.String type,
                     nl.group11.planplan.APIHandler.Callback<java.util.List<nl.group11.planplan.GooglePlace>> callback,
                     java.lang.String pagetoken)
        Queries Google Places Web Service API, using the specified pagetoken to get the next pages of an original query, when the page token is not equal to "". When pagetoken is equal to "", a normal query is performed using the given parameters.
        Parameters:
        pagetoken - the page token which specifies the page to get from an original query ( as received along with the results of the original query). See also queryGooglePlaces(String, int, String, Callback)
